---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Masters Gallery Foods — Customer Story — Formic"
  description="Masters Gallery Foods automated palletizing at its California plant — taking 40-pound lifts off 160 employees moving 18M+ pounds of cheese a year, and moving people into better roles."
  ogTitle="Masters Gallery Foods — Formic Customer Story"
  ogDescription="18M+ lbs/yr · 160 employees · zero upfront CapEx"
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/stories/masters-gallery" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/stories">Customer Stories</a><span class="sep">/</span>Masters Gallery Foods
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Customer Story · Masters Gallery Foods</div>
    <h1 style="font-size:clamp(32px,3.8vw,56px)">When Leadership and Employees Align: Masters Gallery Automates Palletizing to Make Work Better for Everyone</h1>
    <p class="lede">At its California plant, Masters Gallery Foods moves more than 18 million pounds of cheese a year with 160 people working around the clock. Automating palletizing took the 40-pound lifts off their backs — and moved them into better roles.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <img src="/stories/masters-gallery-hero.jpg" alt="Masters Gallery Foods automated palletizing" />
      <span class="dv-cap">Masters Gallery Foods · California</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white" style="padding:64px 0 0">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 80px">
    <div class="db-tag">At a glance</div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(150px,1fr));gap:1px;background:var(--lgrey);border:1px solid var(--lgrey);margin-top:14px">
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Founded</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">1974</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Locations</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">Wisconsin & California</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Industry</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">Cheese & packaging</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Employees</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">160</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Annual volume</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">18M+ lbs</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — The Challenge</div>
      <h2>40-pound boxes, <em>all shift long</em>.</h2>
      <p>Family-owned since 1974, Masters Gallery Foods supplies private-brand retail, foodservice, and wholesale distributors from Wisconsin and California. Its California facility moves more than 18 million pounds of product a year with 160 employees working around the clock — and palletizing meant lifting 40-pound boxes and bending to the floor again and again across eight-hour shifts.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>18M+ lbs of product a year, 160 employees around the clock</li>
        <li>40-pound boxes lifted across full 8-hour shifts</li>
        <li>Manual stacking straining frontline backs</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/stories/masters-gallery-2.jpg" alt="Masters Gallery Foods packaging and palletizing line" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Cheese · packaged & palletized</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0143.jpg" alt="Formic Full Service palletizing cell" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Full Service · fixed monthly</span></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — The Solution</div>
      <h2>Right for employees, <em>right for the business</em>.</h2>
      <p>Without the capital to drop equipment in, leadership chose Formic's Full Service model — equipment, service, maintenance, and performance commitments for a fixed monthly rate, no large outlay. Frontline workers weren't replaced; they were reallocated to less strenuous roles, including line-leader positions.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Fixed monthly rate — no large capital outlay</li>
        <li>Equipment, service, maintenance, and performance covered</li>
        <li>Workers moved into line-leader and less strenuous roles</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white" style="padding:88px 80px">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:0">
    <div class="pull-quote">
      <blockquote>"Automation is about health for our employees. Companies will say, 'Our employees are our number one priority,' but if you don't walk the walk, can you really believe that?"</blockquote>
      <cite>Patrick Henson · General Manager, Masters Gallery Foods</cite>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:80px;text-align:center">
    <div class="db-tag" style="justify-content:center">03 — The Outcome</div>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:clamp(40px,5vw,72px);font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.02em;line-height:1;color:var(--white);margin:18px 0 56px">Nobody fired. <em style="color:var(--orange);font-style:normal">Everybody better off.</em></h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.1)">
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">18M+</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Lbs moved per year</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">160</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Employees, around the clock</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">$0</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Upfront CapEx</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>Make work <em>better for everyone</em>.</h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="mailto:sales@formic.co" class="btn-ctadark">Get Started</a>
    <a href="/stories" class="btn-ctawh">More Customer Stories</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
